- I know.

26:23.832 --> 26:26.166
I'm good for it. Wait a minute,
I'm good for it, Pouchy. You know me.

26:26.251 --> 26:28.335
Pouchy, please. Wait a minute, Pouchy.

26:28.378 --> 26:30.713
One more week
I'll get you your money. Okay.

26:30.797 --> 26:32.172
Okay, okay.

26:32.465 --> 26:35.884
Pouchy, please.
One more week, man. Okay! Give me a minute!

26:35.969 --> 26:38.178
Don't cut it. Okay, all right.

26:38.346 --> 26:40.347
I'll give the money. Okay.

26:40.515 --> 26:43.017
Okay, give me a minute.
I just need the time.

26:48.064 --> 26:49.356
I'm good.

26:54.279 --> 26:55.362
Okay.

26:55.864 --> 26:58.032
One chocolate bar each.

26:58.575 --> 26:59.908
That's it.

27:00.535 --> 27:01.619
Okay.

27:02.704 --> 27:04.705
Hold your sister's hand.

27:05.540 --> 27:08.042
- Okay? And don't talk to anybody.
- Okay, Mom.

27:08.543 --> 27:10.336
- I love you.
- Love you too, Mom.

27:23.058 --> 27:25.643
Uh, deterrents or surveillance?

27:26.102 --> 27:27.686
Surveillance, please.

27:27.937 --> 27:29.188
Something small.

27:31.024 --> 27:33.192
You mean something like this?

27:33.276 --> 27:35.569
Wireless, discrete.

27:35.862 --> 27:37.529
They call it the nanny cam.

27:37.989 --> 27:39.657
Sometimes the nanny's pinching
your valuables,

27:39.741 --> 27:42.076
sometimes your husband's
pinching the nanny, you know?

27:43.745 --> 27:45.537
Just show me how it works, please.

27:56.257 --> 27:58.300
Stay in school.

28:00.387 --> 28:01.929
I mean it, buddy.

28:17.779 --> 28:19.113
Sarah?

28:22.659 --> 28:23.784
Sarah?

28:25.620 --> 28:26.704
Sarah.

28:30.458 --> 28:32.334
Sarah, hey, Sarah.

28:34.212 --> 28:35.629
Sarah, you're alive!

28:36.464 --> 28:37.589
Sarah, it's me.

28:39.217 --> 28:40.384
Look at me.

28:41.136 --> 28:42.636
I don't...

28:44.139 --> 28:46.557
- I don't know who you are.
- You bitch, you faked it.

28:46.641 --> 28:49.476
- You've got the wrong person.
- You faked it, you bitch!

28:49.561 --> 28:52.896
How could you do this to me?
Sarah, I thought you were dead.

28:52.981 --> 28:55.858
How could you goddamn do this to me?

28:57.485 --> 28:59.987
My eyes! Ah, you bitch!

29:01.364 --> 29:02.865
--Ah!

29:05.285 --> 29:08.120
- Ah, there you are.
- Goddamn it. Goddamn...

29:08.413 --> 29:10.497
Okay, it's a race into the car.

29:10.540 --> 29:12.499
- Me, me. First me.
- Sarah!

29:12.584 --> 29:14.460
Hey, whoever gets in first, wins.

29:14.502 --> 29:17.337
- Who's that guy?
- Uh, Sarah...

29:17.839 --> 29:19.006
You bitch.

29:23.386 --> 29:25.012
Hello, Alison.

29:25.180 --> 29:28.891
I was just assaulted by
a disgusting thug who thought I was you.

29:29.350 --> 29:30.893
Who? What'd he look like?

29:30.977 --> 29:32.144
I don't know, he was...

29:33.271 --> 29:34.396
Urban.

29:34.647 --> 29:35.939
What the hell does that mean?

29:36.441 --> 29:38.066
Not white, okay.

29:38.777 --> 29:40.903
Oh, shit! Vic.

29:41.863 --> 29:43.280
Wha... What happened?

29:43.448 --> 29:45.616
I assaulted him back is what happened.

29:46.326 --> 29:47.910
Please tell me that's not Kira's father.

29:48.077 --> 29:50.954
No, no. Absolutely not.

29:52.373 --> 29:53.916
Well, what's going on with Paul?

29:54.000 --> 29:57.044
Well, we think Beth was spying on him.

29:57.587 --> 29:58.921
We found surveillance gear.

29:59.005 --> 30:00.422
She never told me about that.

30:01.508 --> 30:03.967
Is it true? Is he a mole?

30:04.052 --> 30:05.511
I don't know that yet.

30:06.846 --> 30:08.222
What's going on with you?

30:08.473 --> 30:11.725
Nothing, I'm fine.
Call me when you know something for sure.

30:18.233 --> 30:19.399
Olivier?

30:21.903 --> 30:23.070
Paul.

30:24.823 --> 30:26.532
What are you doing here?
Is something wrong?

30:27.200 --> 30:28.784
We need to talk about Beth.

30:30.912 --> 30:32.371
How was she this morning?

30:33.540 --> 30:35.749
Fine. Everything's fine.

30:42.298 --> 30:45.384
You don't do
this sort of thing much, do you?

30:46.427 --> 30:47.928
You mean with a live person?

30:49.222 --> 30:50.973
Oh! Right...

30:51.224 --> 30:52.599
Morgue humor.

30:53.101 --> 30:54.518
You're awfully cute.

30:55.603 --> 30:56.728
Okay.

30:59.858 --> 31:01.441
Okay, bye.

31:01.943 --> 31:03.110
Bye.

31:09.993 --> 31:12.119
The morgue attendant? Really?

31:12.245 --> 31:14.830
- Can you knock?
- Brilliant, Fe.

31:14.914 --> 31:17.916
Shagging the bloke that
we conned into identifying my body.

31:18.209 --> 31:21.169
Colin is the first nice boy I've met in ages.

31:21.504 --> 31:23.630
- What? Like six weeks?
- No.

31:24.090 --> 31:26.258
- At least eight.
- Where do you think this is gonna go?

31:26.301 --> 31:28.176
- Hey?
- Oh, my God!

31:28.261 --> 31:30.637
I'm so sorry, I completely
forgot rule number one.

31:30.722 --> 31:33.265
That your life is always more
important than mine.

31:33.474 --> 31:35.642
No, it's just way more difficult.

31:36.477 --> 31:38.520
- Vic is back.
- No shit?

31:38.688 --> 31:41.398
Yeah, he ran into Alison
so he thinks I'm alive.

31:42.483 --> 31:44.276
I'll figure it out. I'll...

31:45.153 --> 31:46.987
I need to know what happened
at Paul's office.

31:47.405 --> 31:50.324
Sorry. I've been a bit busy, haven't I?

31:51.701 --> 31:53.619
Well, it did record something.

32:02.003 --> 32:03.712
What are you doing here?
Is something wrong?

32:04.297 --> 32:06.590
- This is it.
- We need to talk about Beth.

32:07.508 --> 32:11.094
- How was she this morning?
- Fine. Everything's fine.

32:11.512 --> 32:13.931
You still concerned about
her mental health?

32:15.016 --> 32:17.517
- No, she's better.
- Suddenly better?

32:18.436 --> 32:21.438
You understand your role as
monitor is not to interfere...

32:21.522 --> 32:22.689
Monitor?

32:23.066 --> 32:26.360
If there's anything pertinent
I should know, anything at all...

32:26.402 --> 32:28.028
If there were, I would tell you.

32:31.866 --> 32:33.075
Oh, shit! it's him.

32:33.409 --> 32:34.785
No, don't answer that.

32:35.036 --> 32:36.078
No!

32:36.162 --> 32:37.746
- Hello.
- Beth...

32:37.914 --> 32:40.290
- Where are you?
- Out. Where are you?

32:40.500 --> 32:41.833
We have to talk.

32:42.627 --> 32:44.711
- About what?
- I need you to come home.

32:45.254 --> 32:46.713
Yeah, I don't think so.

32:54.555 --> 32:55.847
He knows something.

32:56.224 --> 32:57.849
Well, you can't go back there. You know that.

32:58.393 --> 32:59.643
No, I can't.

33:06.901 --> 33:08.235
Oh, shit.

33:08.861 --> 33:11.780
- Oh, my God!
- Paul followed me straight to Kira.

33:16.577 --> 33:17.911
Is this a bad time?

33:24.168 --> 33:26.461
You tased me, you maced me.

33:26.921 --> 33:28.422
And you think I'm just gonna...

33:29.298 --> 33:31.425
I'm just gonna walk away, like I'm nobody?

33:32.427 --> 33:34.594
- I was working a job.
- Uh-huh.

33:34.679 --> 33:35.721
Oh, yeah?

33:35.763 --> 33:37.097
Yeah, you would have ruined the whole thing.

33:37.181 --> 33:38.348
Yeah?

33:38.808 --> 33:40.559
I guess you're on a roll now, huh, Sarah?

33:43.146 --> 33:45.105
And that coke that you stole from me?

33:46.607 --> 33:48.025
Pretending to be dead.

33:49.110 --> 33:50.944
Who do you think took the fall for that?

33:51.487 --> 33:52.654
Huh?

33:53.990 --> 33:55.449
Pouchy took my finger.

33:57.243 --> 33:59.828
If I don't come up with 15K...

34:00.246 --> 34:01.455
He's gonna lobster me.

34:01.539 --> 34:03.999
A finger every week
until all I have left is a lobster claw.

34:04.083 --> 34:05.667
Sit down, sit down.

34:05.752 --> 34:07.461
Do you want the money or not?

34:17.304 --> 34:18.804
There's 20K.

34:18.889 --> 34:21.850
Fifteen for your debt and then
five for your pain and suffering.

34:22.351 --> 34:24.061
It must have been some play.

34:25.646 --> 34:26.938
Uh-uh.

34:27.482 --> 34:30.525
This is piss-off money, okay?
You don't get to know anything.

34:32.110 --> 34:34.112
I'm entitled to know everything.

34:36.239 --> 34:38.784
Can I ask you a question? How do you do it?

34:40.495 --> 34:42.245
Lying there in that morgue?

34:42.830 --> 34:46.333
Holding your breath, Sarah,
while I am bawling?

34:46.876 --> 34:49.293
I'm crying like a goddamn child.

34:52.422 --> 34:53.965
You know what's crazy?

34:54.217 --> 34:55.926
You know how stupid I am?

34:56.677 --> 34:58.678
I'm standing here looking at you

34:59.472 --> 35:01.348
and all I keep thinking about is Myrtle Beach.

35:02.058 --> 35:05.060
- You remember?
- Out. Yeah, that was a long time ago, Vic.

35:05.353 --> 35:07.896
I was working with that mook Angel,
he got you in with the carnies.

35:08.189 --> 35:09.773
I'm not proud of what we did.

35:09.982 --> 35:11.191
We were on top of the world, Sarah.

35:11.234 --> 35:12.400
We were parasites.

35:12.485 --> 35:13.902
No. We were in love.

35:14.403 --> 35:15.612
Not me.

35:16.322 --> 35:17.781
Ever.

35:22.578 --> 35:23.995
I think, she means it, Victor.

35:24.956 --> 35:26.623
You want that money?

35:27.250 --> 35:28.792
Take it and go now.

35:31.045 --> 35:32.379
Right now, Vic!

35:33.965 --> 35:35.090
Okay.

35:38.636 --> 35:40.137
It's not over, Sarah.

35:46.060 --> 35:49.396
Is every man in your life
a complete wanker, except me?

35:49.939 --> 35:51.731
I need you to go to S's house.

35:52.733 --> 35:54.651
Make sure Kira's okay. Yeah?

35:54.902 --> 35:56.653
You're not going back to Paul's.

35:56.737 --> 35:58.029
I will not let him threaten my daughter.

35:58.072 --> 35:59.656
Sarah, you're not going back to Paul's.

35:59.740 --> 36:00.949
Sarah!

36:28.686 --> 36:30.187
No, it's fine. Don't worry.

36:31.314 --> 36:33.273
If anything else comes up, I'll let you know.

36:58.466 --> 37:00.008
- Felix called yet?
- Yeah.

37:00.092 --> 37:02.260
He just played me the recording.
I heard everything.

37:02.303 --> 37:03.637
Um, where are you?

37:03.679 --> 37:06.348
I'm about to go in,
and shoot Paul in the balls.

37:06.432 --> 37:07.641
Wait, Sarah.

37:07.683 --> 37:09.476
This is our chance to get answers.

37:09.644 --> 37:11.394
He followed me to Kira, Cos.

37:11.479 --> 37:14.648
I know, I know.
But he also covered for you. Right?

37:14.732 --> 37:18.610
That Olivier guy, he asked if anything was
wrong and Paul said no. Why?

37:18.903 --> 37:23.156
Because, I think
he might be falling for fake Beth.

37:23.282 --> 37:26.159
Yes! That's awesome.
That... You can use that.

37:26.452 --> 37:28.870
Who do you think
got me into this mess in the first place? Huh?

37:28.955 --> 37:30.830
Okay. I know. Just chill.

37:31.207 --> 37:34.125
I think that Olivier guy, he runs Paul.

37:34.168 --> 37:37.420
It sounds like some kind of double-blind.

37:37.838 --> 37:39.089
What are you going on about?

37:39.173 --> 37:40.757
They are keeping Paul in the dark too.

37:41.300 --> 37:43.051
Right? So that he can't
skew the results either.

37:45.012 --> 37:47.514
You mean, he may not even
know he's watching a clone?

37:47.598 --> 37:48.848
Yes, right.

37:49.308 --> 37:51.017
But Olivier definitely knows.

37:51.852 --> 37:53.395
Okay, he's the one that we need to get to.

37:53.729 --> 37:55.021
You mind if I get through Paul first?

37:55.106 --> 37:56.356
- Sarah?

38:11.455 --> 38:12.747
I'll sleep on the couch.

38:12.832 --> 38:14.916
Donnie, Donnie.

38:15.001 --> 38:16.710
You're right.

38:18.671 --> 38:20.422
Everyone deserves their privacy.

38:23.050 --> 38:24.175
Come.

38:45.448 --> 38:47.824
I thought you handed in your sidearm.

38:47.908 --> 38:48.908
Huh?

38:48.951 --> 38:51.036
Left jacket pocket, hanging low.

38:52.496 --> 38:54.914
Well, apparently, I've got a stalker.

38:58.210 --> 38:59.336
Sit.

39:02.631 --> 39:03.757
Put it on the table.

39:11.474 --> 39:12.974
I knew.

39:13.059 --> 39:15.435
I couldn't put my finger on it, but I knew.

39:16.771 --> 39:18.813
It was that day
you were supposed to do the hearing,

39:18.939 --> 39:20.231
first time we had sex in months.

39:20.941 --> 39:21.941
What? I missed you.

39:22.026 --> 39:23.818
You were wearing that Clash t-shirt.

39:23.903 --> 39:25.945
I was like, "What?"

39:26.947 --> 39:29.699
And then, wham, you screw me,
right on the kitchen counter.

39:31.118 --> 39:33.453
You complaining, Paul?
What are you saying?

39:33.537 --> 39:34.621
You quit the force.

39:35.122 --> 39:37.290
After refusing ever even to think it.

39:38.000 --> 39:39.209
You know what I've been through.

39:39.293 --> 39:41.878
And then the scar on your neck
just disappears. Because of what?

39:42.880 --> 39:44.297
Some cream?

39:44.757 --> 39:45.799
And now...

39:50.137 --> 39:51.513
This little girl.

39:53.641 --> 39:55.975
I was there when Beth
found out she couldn't have kids.

39:58.562 --> 40:00.188
So, who is this girl?

40:01.190 --> 40:02.524
She's my half-sister.

40:03.234 --> 40:04.609
I watched you together.

40:05.152 --> 40:06.653
She's your daughter, isn't she?

40:07.947 --> 40:09.531
You're losing it.

40:09.615 --> 40:10.824
Am I?

40:11.200 --> 40:12.867
I was looking at some old video today.

40:12.952 --> 40:14.869
You were training for that

40:14.954 --> 40:16.162
half-marathon.

40:16.831 --> 40:18.248
What was the last race you ran?

40:21.335 --> 40:22.544
What city was it in?

40:29.760 --> 40:31.261
Where is Beth?

40:38.144 --> 40:39.936
One last time,

40:41.689 --> 40:43.148
whoever you are,

40:44.483 --> 40:45.733
where is Beth?

40:46.110 --> 40:47.444
She killed herself.

40:48.904 --> 40:50.405
She jumped in front of a train.

40:51.532 --> 40:52.532
You're English.

40:53.868 --> 40:55.577
Who are you?

40:55.661 --> 40:56.661
I'm her twin.

40:57.163 --> 40:58.455
Twin?

41:00.082 --> 41:01.499
Is this a test?

41:02.168 --> 41:03.418
A test of what?

41:03.502 --> 41:04.919
Beth didn't have a sister.

41:06.464 --> 41:08.131
What's your name?

41:08.215 --> 41:09.299
Sarah.

41:09.383 --> 41:10.550
Sarah what?

41:11.260 --> 41:12.886
Sarah's good enough.

41:14.305 --> 41:16.556
When Beth died, I took her identity.

41:17.099 --> 41:18.141
Beth isn't dead.

41:21.770 --> 41:24.397
Look, I was just gonna
clean out her bank accounts.

41:24.482 --> 41:27.066
I didn't mean to get all tangled up with you.

41:28.027 --> 41:30.612
If she really is dead,
how do I know you didn't kill her?

41:30.821 --> 41:32.238
- 'Cause you killed her.
- What?

41:33.240 --> 41:35.074
You're her monitor, aren't you?

41:36.327 --> 41:37.660
And what's that?

41:37.745 --> 41:38.912
You observe her.

41:39.622 --> 41:41.873
You let people into her home.

41:42.541 --> 41:44.125
Like last night.

41:45.503 --> 41:48.546
Doctors came and medically
examined her in her sleep.

41:50.132 --> 41:51.883
And she knew.

41:58.265 --> 42:01.476
You're a plant and she killed herself

42:01.560 --> 42:04.729
because the man that she loved
turned her whole life into a lie.

42:05.940 --> 42:09.442
She knew you didn't love her and she couldn't
understand why you wouldn't leave.

42:09.610 --> 42:11.027
And now she figured it out.

42:11.820 --> 42:13.196
This isn't true.

42:15.074 --> 42:16.616
It is a sick test,

42:18.285 --> 42:19.410
isn't it?

42:20.955 --> 42:22.455
Isn't it?

42:23.332 --> 42:24.791
She trusted you.

42:26.460 --> 42:28.670
How could you do that to her?

42:34.635 --> 42:36.261
You think I had a choice.

42:38.597 --> 42:39.973
Just tell me why?

42:41.767 --> 42:43.476
They don't tell us why.

42:53.779 --> 42:55.655
Where did you go in the middle
of the night, Donnie?

42:55.739 --> 42:57.282
I don't know, Never Never Land.

42:57.324 --> 42:58.324
What's the emergency?

42:59.660 --> 43:01.327
- Hi.
- We're not late for the potluck?

43:01.412 --> 43:03.580
I may have a monitor dilemma of my own.

43:03.706 --> 43:06.916
It's really nice to make
a friend in the brave new world.

43:08.752 --> 43:10.003
That is a really good look on you.
